The paper also mentions game semantics, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with graphs and cliques, which are topics in computer science, specifically in graph theory and algorithms, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions finite multisets, which are a data structure in computer science, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the co-free exponential, which is a topic in information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category as well.
